    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-11T09:18:26+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-11T09:18:26+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-10T23:48:26Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-10T23:48:26Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front in the Bight will move across the south of SA today followed by a weaker front on Monday. A high pressure system centred near southern WA will begin to dominate the weather pattern across SA mid next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Medium chance of showers south of Woomera, becoming less likely in the late afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds west to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h increasing to 35 km/h before turning south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the late morning and afternoon. Daytime maximum temperatures between 17 and 22.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:00am to 2:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 4 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-12T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-13T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-11T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-12T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog north of Coober Pedy. Slight chance of a shower south of Woomera, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds southeast to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h tending west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h before dawn then becoming light in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 4 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-13T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-14T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-12T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-13T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Woomera, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Light winds becoming west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 4 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-14T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-15T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-13T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-14T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Coober Pedy. Slight chance of a shower south of Woomera, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds west to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h turning south to southeasterly during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
